Moving normal int literal fixes to fix_int and making explicit.
In all cases but repr(), 3.x int is the same as 2.x long, but repr() is enough of a reason to make this explicit.

fix_print is more elegant now.  test_print is cooler, but still tests the same stuff.
fix_print now effectively discards every match after it makes the first fix of the tree.
fix_print saves the first node of the tree to a variable that is modified, instead of looking for it every time and comparing to the fixed one.
Altogether, these fix_print changes bring it from O(n^2) to O(n).

commit_message:
Remove feature_base and fix_features

Support is being dropped for versions of Python
below 2.7, so these modules are obsolete now.

- Remove `feature_base.py`
- Remove `fix_features.py`
    - It had imported code from `feature_base.py`

Fixes: #17
Run build workflow on PRs

Rearrange fixers into separate package

The intent here is to move towards being able to ship custom
"fixer suits" in a similar manner to how pytest can do its plugins.
Ideally we can automate discovery in the future.

This is a large changeset but is almost entirely just the moving
of files and updating imports and paths to reflect the new organization.
